---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CTAButton from "../components/CTAButton.astro";
import FAQSection from "../components/FAQSection.astro";
import { FaEnvelope } from "react-icons/fa";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Engineering Leadership Weekly | Jade Rubick - Engineering Leadership"
  description="Weekly newsletter on engineering leadership by Jade Rubick"
>
  <div class="newsletter-page">
    <header class="newsletter-header">
      <h1>Engineering Leadership Weekly</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="newsletter-content">
      <p>I offer a weekly newsletter on leadership:</p>

      <CTAButton
        href="https://rubick.ck.page/products/engineering-leadership-course"
        mainText="Get Engineering Leadership Weekly"
        subText="Supporter Edition"
        variant="primary"
      >
        <FaEnvelope slot="icon" size={48} />
      </CTAButton>

      <CTAButton
        href="/"
        mainText="Get the Free Version"
        subText="Standard Edition"
        variant="secondary"
        isExternal={false}
      >
        <FaEnvelope slot="icon" size={48} />
      </CTAButton>

      <p>
        The newsletter basically feeds you most of the content from my blog, but
        on a weekly schedule.
      </p>

      <picture>
        <source
          srcset="/images/sarah-400.webp"
          type="image/webp"
        />
        <img
          src="/images/sarah.png"
          alt="Newsletter illustration"
          class="newsletter-image"
        />
      </picture>

      <h2>About the newsletter</h2>

      <FAQSection>
        <dt>
          How is the paid version of Engineering Leadership Weekly different
          than the free version?
        </dt>
        <dd>It's not different. But the paid version supports my writing.</dd>

        <dt>Where do I sign up for the free version?</dt>
        <dd>
          It is on the <a href="/">main page</a> of rubick.com
        </dd>

        <dt>How much email will I be receiving, and for how long?</dt>
        <dd>
          Engineering Leadership Weekly is a weekly email with almost two weeks's
          content.
          <br />
          <br />
          When you get to the end, you'll get less frequent emails, since I write
          less frequently than once a week.
        </dd>

        <dt>Can I sign up for both the newsletter and course?</dt>
        <dd>
          You can, but if you're thinking about that, I would just sign up for
          the course. At the end of the course, you will automatically
          transition into receiving the newsletter. You will get a few duplicate
          emails, but not many.
        </dd>

        <dt>
          If I pay for the newsletter and don't like it, can I get a refund?
        </dt>
        <dd>
          Yes, I provide refunds with no questions asked, for two months after
          the newsletter starts. <a href="/contact/">Contact me</a>.
        </dd>

        <dt>Is it annoying to unsubscribe if I'm finished with it?</dt>
        <dd>Every email has an unsubscribe link in it. It should be super easy.</dd>

        <dt>How do I give you feedback on any of the newsletter content?</dt>
        <dd>
          You can reply to any email and I'll read it. I really appreciate
          feedback!
        </dd>

        <dt>
          How relevant is this content for non-engineering managers and leaders?
        </dt>
        <dd>
          Ironically, the Engineering Leadership Weekly is LESS engineering
          focused than the name suggests. Almost all the content is valuable to
          leaders from a design or product management background. Around half of
          the content could be valuable outside of a product development
          organization, for managers and leaders from many places. Just keep in
          mind you may need to adopt the content more to your local situation.
        </dd>
      </FAQSection>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .newsletter-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .newsletter-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-l);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .newsletter-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--heading-size-h1);
    line-height: var(--heading-line-height-h1);
    color: var(--text-color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-m);
  }

  .newsletter-content {
    font-size: var(--font-size-s);
    line-height: var(--text-line-height-default);
  }

  .newsletter-content p {
    margin: 0 0 1.5em;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .newsletter-content h2 {
    font-size: var(--heading-size-h2);
    line-height: var(--heading-line-height-h2);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-neutral-gray-j);
    margin: 1.5em 0 0.75em;
  }

  .newsletter-content a {
    color: var(--color-brand-primary);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .newsletter-content a:hover {
    color: var(--color-brand-hover);
  }

  .newsletter-image {
    width: 100%;
    margin: var(--space-l) 0;
    border-radius: var(--size-radius-default);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .newsletter-content {
      padding: 0 var(--space-m);
    }
  }
</style>
